Article Title: Ukraine Renews Push to Get Its Grain Out to the World
Article Snippet: After a journey of 12 hours across waters caught up in the war, a ship carrying tons of wheat made it safely to Romanian waters, as Kyiv worked to transport grain overland, as well.
Author: By Matthew Mpoke Bigg

Article Title: Ukraine’s Fight Is the World’s, Zelensky Tells U.N. Assembly
Article Snippet: Painting Vladimir Putin’s Russia as a nation that seeks to dominate others, President Volodymyr Zelensky cast his appeal for broad support as a matter of global security.
Author: By Richard Pérez-Peña, Andrew E. Kramer and Farnaz Fassihi

Article Title: Wednesday Briefing: Zelensky’s Warning at the U.N.
Article Snippet: Plus, new discoveries about a nomadic clan on the island of Borneo.
Author: By Justin Porter

Article Title: Russia’s Aggression Is a Threat to the World, Zelensky Says
Article Snippet: In a speech at the U.N. General Assembly, President Volodymyr Zelensky of Ukraine painted Russia as a habitual aggressor that has weaponized nuclear energy and essentials like food and water.
Author: By Reuters

Article Title: Ukraine’s Counteroffensive Looms Large as Zelensky Addresses U.N.
Article Snippet: The effort to drive Russian forces from Ukraine’s south and east has been slow and bloody. Here’s a look at what might come next in the campaign.
Author: By German Lopez

Article Title: Britain Passes Sweeping New Online Safety Law
Article Snippet: The far-reaching bill had set off debates about balancing free speech and privacy rights against efforts to halt the spread of harmful content online.
Author: By Adam Satariano

Article Title: ‘The Fossil Fuel Age Has Failed,’ Guterres Tells World Leaders
Article Snippet: António Guterres, the United Nations secretary general, called on nations to phase out the burning of coal, oil and gas.
Author: By Reuters

Article Title: Ancient Earthworks Trodden by Golfers Become a World Heritage Site
Article Snippet: The UNESCO World Heritage Committee has recognized the Octagon Earthworks in central Ohio as a cultural marvel.
Author: By Sarah Bahr

Article Title: Biden Aides and Saudis Explore Defense Treaty Modeled After Asian Pacts
Article Snippet: Despite U.S. fatigue over Middle East wars, the White House sees a security agreement resembling those with Japan or South Korea as an incentive for Saudi Arabia to normalize relations with Israel.
Author: By Edward Wong and Mark Mazzetti

Article Title: Biden, in U.N. Speech, Calls for Action on Ukraine and Other Crises
Article Snippet: As other major leaders skipped the annual opening session of the General Assembly, Mr. Biden used his address to try to counter war fatigue both at home and abroad.
Author: By Michael D. Shear and Peter Baker
